{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17599000","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17599000"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T11:47:48+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T11:47:48+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15517"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15517","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15517"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.04,0.75,0.1,0,0.1]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8208"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"82120"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"8208","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/8208"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15517"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"67316"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4927"},{"type":"tags","id":"4929"},{"type":"tags","id":"4942"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"9905"},{"type":"tags","id":"9924"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"19859"},{"type":"contributions","id":"19861"},{"type":"contributions","id":"27986"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"82120","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/82120"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EThe effects of obesity on respiratory function can be significant. The mechanical effects of the increased body mass can contribute to various breathing difficulties.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the effect of obesity on chest wall mechanics?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["No change in chest wall mechanics","Decreased chest wall compliance","Decreased chest wall elastic recoil","Decreased chest wall mass","Increased chest wall compliance"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EIn obesity, \u003Cstrong\u003Edecreased chest wall compliance\u003C/strong\u003E occurs due to increased adipose tissue deposition around the chest and abdomen. This makes the chest wall more rigid and requires greater effort to expand during inspiration.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe statement that there is \u003Cstrong\u003Edecreased chest wall elastic recoil\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect - elastic recoil actually increases in obesity. \u003Cstrong\u003EIncreased chest wall compliance\u003C/strong\u003E is the opposite of what occurs. There is definitely \u003Cstrong\u003Echange in chest wall mechanics\u003C/strong\u003E, so this is incorrect. \u003Cstrong\u003EDecreased chest wall mass\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect as obesity increases chest wall mass through fat deposition.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe decreased compliance leads to increased work of breathing, contributing to dyspnoea and reduced exercise tolerance in obesity.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Obesity decreases chest wall compliance due to increased adipose tissue and mechanical load","Decreased chest wall compliance in obesity leads to increased work of breathing","Elastic recoil of the chest wall is increased in obesity, not decreased"],"references":["Dixon AE, Peters U. The effect of obesity on lung function. Expert Rev Respir Med. 2018 Sep;12(9):755-767. doi: 10.1080/17476348.2018.1506331. Epub 2018 Aug 14. PMID: 30056777; PMCID: PMC6311385.","Lo Mauro A, Tringali G, Codecasa F, Abbruzzese L, Sartorio A, Aliverti A. Pulmonary and chest wall function in obese adults. Sci Rep. 2023 Oct 18;13(1):17753. doi: 10.1038/s41598-023-44222-3. PMID: 37852999; PMCID: PMC10585005.","Littleton SW. Impact of obesity on respiratory function. Respirology. 2012 Jan;17(1):43-9. doi: 10.1111/j.1440-1843.2011.02096.x. PMID: 22040049.","Kumar, V., Abbas, A. K., \u0026 Aster, J. C. (Eds.). (2012). Robbins basic pathology e-book. Elsevier Health Science"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"67316"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15517"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"67316","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/67316"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-28T11:16:13+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-28T11:16:42+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8208"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"82120"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"7"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"4927","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/4927"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udec1","name":"Respiratory","synonyms":[],"description":null,"posi